 You need to read the strategy for PoH as reference:<br>
 <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://pub64.ezboard.com/ftavernheroesfrm5.showMessage?topicID=3.topic">pub64.ezboard.com/ftavern...ID=3.topic</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
 <br>
 The big difference between PoH and PoF is the break in.<br>
 When we'll enter in PoF the zone will be all up, and there will be a lot of roamers close to the west camp.<br>
 So the first step is to kill all the roamers as fast as we can.<br>
 <br>
 Tank will be bind in oggok and caster just before the gate, you have 50% chance to die there. Please all bind there.<br>
 <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>      1 - Break in </b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
 All the groups must have:  be full buff, See Invi and Invi. No Levitate.<br>
 <br>
 Just after zone in is: go left up to the west wall, see map.<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>     ---- If you get attacked, DO NOT TRAIN CAMP, stop where you are and do /loc and wait to die. ----</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
 <br>
 For the break in we'll make special group and a special strategy.<br>
 <br>
 - Groups - <br>
 We'll do the break in with 3 groups maximum, the higher lvls.<br>
 Each group will have a big tank and a cleric.<br>
 Each group will have 2 evac (wiz or druid), on of the evac is the main evac.<br>
 <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>     The main evac do not do anything except evac. To be clear the main evac do not:<br>
 - sit,<br>
 - cast a buff,<br>
 - heal someone,<br>
 - DD or DoT a mob,<br>
 - attack with a weapon,<br>
 ....</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
 The goal of the main evac is to be sure he can evac whatever happens.<br>
 If the main evac is kill on the way to the camp the second evac become main evac.<br>
 <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>     During all the break in nobody sit for med, you have to enter in PoF FM. </b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
 Nobody DoT during the break-in, we can't allow any assist problem.<br>
 The fight themself are standard: assist well, keep enchants and tanks alive.<br>
 If one mez is break at this step we can fail the break in.<br>
 <br>
 The raid commander will shout an evac order when: we have too many mobs at camp, or when everybody is oom.<br>
 The evac must be cast by both evac in each group: main and second.<br>
 Then we'll run as fast as we can to come back to PoF entrance, wait all are ready an re go in and try again.<br>
 <br>
 When all the roamers will be dead the break in will be finish and then everybody will be able to enter in PoF.<br>
 Like this the break in can be done in 1h to 30 mins.<br>
 <br>
 If this fail for any reason we'll have corpses at West camp, those corpses can't be resu before the break in is over.<br>
 So if we fail this part you will have to be very patient because the break in can last few hours.<br>
 <br>
 <br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>      2 - Chat Channel usage</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
see PoH post<br>
 <br>
 <br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>      3 - Roles of each class</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
see PoH post<br>
 <br>
 <br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>      4 - General rules</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
- always assit the main tank,<br>
- do not cast just when you have a target let the tank aggro the mob and Slow, Malo, Snare and root go in,<br>
- cast DD in melee range always to avoid movement of the mob,<br>
- do not cast any area effect spells,<br>
- before cast a DoT be sure you are on the right target, wait the mob lost one bubble of life,<br>
- all spells that don't do damage don't break mez but change agro, so rangers will snare and paladin will root even mez mobs, so if a mez is break the mob will fight them and not the enchant,<br>
- spells that not break mez are: Snare, Root (from Paladin, Cleric and Wizard), Stun, <br>
- we'll have at least 2 puller and 1 rogue so we'll not stop fight if the puller die,<br>
- we'll not stop pull for a die,<br>
- if you think you'll die far from the camp, do /loc before die so we'll find your corpse fast,<br>
- enchanter must stay alive,<br>
 <br>
 <br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>      5 - Emergency: train</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
The only way out is very far from the entrance and all safe camps, so if we have a trouble we'll evac.<br>
All wizard and Druid will need to have an evac all the time ready and have enough mana to cast it. <br>
 <br>
 <br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>      6 - Enchanter Mezz List</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
From harder to kill to the easiers:<br>
Cazic Thule<br>
Terror <br>
Dracoliche<br>
Golem<br>
